using namespace std;
int main() {
    // Declare variables
    string wordToCount; // Declare the word to count
    int count = 0; // Declare the count variable
    // Ask user for the word to count
    cout << "Enter the word to count: ";
    cin >> wordToCount;
    // Open the text file
    ifstream file ("textFile.txt"); // Open the text file

    // Read the lines of the file
    string line;
    while (getline (file, line)) {
        // Count the number of times the word appears in the line
        count += line.find (wordToCount) != string::npos;
        // Print the count
        cout << count << " occurrences of " << wordToCount << " found in the line." << endl;
        // Print the line
        cout << line << endl;
    }

    // Close the file
    file.close();

    return 0;

}
```
This program will open a text file using the `ifstream` class, read each line of the file, and use the `find` function to count the number of times the specified word appears in each line. The count will be printed after each line, along with the line itself. The program will then close the file when it's finished.
